===Noun===
'''phy''' 
# Short for PHYsical layer from the OSI model of network protocols.  The Physical Layer deals with the physical connection of the network and the electrical (or radio) transmission of the bits that meant to be sent and received by the upper layer protocols.  The PHY determines the data rates, frequency used, signaling mechnism, etc.  PHY also refers to the functional circuit or part of a chip or a circuit board that deals with the phsical access, via wires or radio, to the network.  

